parameters: Clea (We need to think of a way to escape)
Clea: It has a pretty sturdy lock, doesn't it?
Thief Nora: Leave it to me!

Thief Nora: Hmm... I can't quite manipulate it well from the
inside... Moreover, I think it's a structurally unique one.

Mage Relm: It's troublesome, isn't it? Let's blow it away
with magic!

Village Chief Olden: I would appreciate it if you refrain
from doing anything that would cause damage here.

Mage Relm: To imprison this genius! Please release me from
here quickly!!
Clea: Please tell us the reason why we were restrained.

Village Chief Olden: ...I suspect that you have a true
purpose. We came here on a request from the Magic Academy.

Village Chief Olden: We cannot release you until those
suspicions are cleared.

Clea: We came here on a request from the Adventurer's Guild,
and we have no other reason.

Clea: Personally, I am searching for something, but it has
nothing to do with the Magic Academy.

Village Chief Olden: Please tell us about your personal
search. There is no emotion as dangerous as selfish
curiosity.
Clea: I am searching for a dragon that killed my parents.
Clea: Could you please let us out of here?

Village Chief Olden: I will open this lock right away, and
there is something I absolutely want to request.

Mage Relm: You can't just capture us and expect us to
believe you have a good reason for it!!

Village Chief Olden: I apologize for the inconvenience, but
please come to Mount Scrilo.

Village Chief Olden: Let me tell you about the big, big
problem that we are facing there.
